WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.358
All right.
Let's just remind ourselves for

00:00:09.358 --> 00:00:13.208
a moment where we were,
and that is that we were

00:00:13.208 --> 00:00:16.402
talking about the structure of
the atom.

00:00:16.402 --> 00:00:19.761
And we talked about how
classical physics,

00:00:19.761 --> 00:00:23.856
the classical mechanics,
classical electromagnetism

00:00:23.856 --> 00:00:28.279
failed to explain how the
electron and the nucleus hung

00:00:28.279 --> 00:00:32.534
together.
And I said that the clues about

00:00:32.534 --> 00:00:37.193
how to solve that conundrum
actually came from a different

00:00:37.193 --> 00:00:41.198
area of discussion,
and that is this wave-particle

00:00:41.198 --> 00:00:44.305
duality.
And so remember that I said we

00:00:44.305 --> 00:00:48.964
are going to put aside that
discussion of the structure of

00:00:48.964 --> 00:00:52.070
the atom all the way until next
Monday.

00:00:52.070 --> 00:00:53.950
Pardon?
No class Monday?

00:00:53.950 --> 00:01:00.000
We're going to put it aside all
the way until next Wednesday.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.072
Thank you.
[LAUGHTER] You sound surprised?

00:01:04.072 --> 00:01:07.649
You're not.
It's a student holiday on

00:01:07.649 --> 00:01:11.225
Monday.
And we're going to talk about

00:01:11.225 --> 00:01:15.695
the wave-particle duality of
light and matter,

00:01:15.695 --> 00:01:21.357
get clues from that area of
discussion, and we're going to

00:01:21.357 --> 00:01:26.125
apply those clues,
then, to solving the structure

00:01:26.125 --> 00:01:31.956
of the atom next Wednesday.
Now, we started on this

00:01:31.956 --> 00:01:37.144
discussion by talking about the
wave-like nature of radiation.

00:01:37.144 --> 00:01:41.737
And to illustrate that,
we did this two-slit experiment

00:01:41.737 --> 00:01:44.798
where we saw an interference
pattern.

00:01:44.798 --> 00:01:49.391
And we talked about how that
interference pattern arose

00:01:49.391 --> 00:01:53.559
because of the property of
superposition of waves.

00:01:53.559 --> 00:01:58.492
That is, if you have waves in
the two same points in space,

00:01:58.492 --> 00:02:03.000
their amplitudes superpose,
or they add.

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:07.059
And because some of those
amplitudes are positive and some

00:02:07.059 --> 00:02:10.192
are negative,
depending on the relative phase

00:02:10.192 --> 00:02:13.112
of the waves,
you have constructive or you

00:02:13.112 --> 00:02:17.314
have destructive interference.
And specifically what we were

00:02:17.314 --> 00:02:20.946
trying to understand is,
in the two-slit experiment,

00:02:20.946 --> 00:02:24.364
why we had this line of bright
spots, dark spots,

00:02:24.364 --> 00:02:27.000
bright spots,
dark spots.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.906
And we analyzed it by drawing
these semicircles,

00:02:30.906 --> 00:02:35.809
which represent the wave front
kind of sneaking through this

00:02:35.809 --> 00:02:40.048
little pinhole here,
this slit, emanating equally in

00:02:40.048 --> 00:02:43.123
all directions.
These semicircles here

00:02:43.123 --> 00:02:48.359
represent the crest of the wave.
The distance here between these

00:02:48.359 --> 00:02:51.434
crests is 1 lambda,
is one wavelength.

00:02:51.434 --> 00:02:56.420
And when we look closely-- Can
we dim the lights in the front

00:02:56.420 --> 00:02:59.455
here?
If you closely,

00:02:59.455 --> 00:03:04.501
what we discovered is that all
points along this line

00:03:04.501 --> 00:03:09.838
constructively interfere.
That is we have waves that are

00:03:09.838 --> 00:03:15.854
at the same place in space and
the maxima and the minima are in

00:03:15.854 --> 00:03:21.094
the same place in space,
and so that's going to lead to

00:03:21.094 --> 00:03:24.684
a very bright spot here on the
screen.

00:03:24.684 --> 00:03:30.409
The amplitude is going to be
twice as high as it was in each

00:03:30.409 --> 00:03:36.211
of the individual waves.
And we get this very bright

00:03:36.211 --> 00:03:39.078
spot.
And we realize that along this

00:03:39.078 --> 00:03:43.583
line, the difference in the
distance traveled by the two

00:03:43.583 --> 00:03:48.006
waves that are constructively
interfering was 1 lambda.

00:03:48.006 --> 00:03:51.037
And then we did so for this
line here.

00:03:51.037 --> 00:03:54.477
And we discovered that all
along this line,

00:03:54.477 --> 00:03:58.000
we had these two waves in
phase.

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:02.483
All along this line we had
constructive interference which,

00:04:02.483 --> 00:04:05.574
of course, imaged as another
bright spot.

00:04:05.574 --> 00:04:09.826
And when we analyzed it,
we found that the difference in

00:04:09.826 --> 00:04:13.768
the distance traveled by the two
waves was 2 lambda.

00:04:13.768 --> 00:04:17.169
And likewise here.
All along this line we had

00:04:17.169 --> 00:04:20.956
constructive interference imaged
as a bright spot.

00:04:20.956 --> 00:04:25.207
And we recognize that in this
case the difference in the

00:04:25.207 --> 00:04:30.000
distance traveled by the two
waves was 0 lambda.

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:34.772
And given that pattern,
we then concluded that there

00:04:34.772 --> 00:04:39.732
was a general condition for
constructive interference.

00:04:39.732 --> 00:04:44.598
That is if you had maximum
constructive interference,

00:04:44.598 --> 00:04:49.090
the general condition that had
to apply was this:

00:04:49.090 --> 00:04:54.144
that the difference in the
distance traveled by the two

00:04:54.144 --> 00:04:58.636
waves was an integral multiple
of the wavelength,

00:04:58.636 --> 00:05:02.660
where this integer N could be
0, or 1, or 2,

00:05:02.660 --> 00:05:06.923
or 3, or 4.
And it's actually symmetric

00:05:06.923 --> 00:05:09.629
here along the center of the two
slits.

00:05:09.629 --> 00:05:14.045
So you would see the same kind
of interference pattern up here.

00:05:14.045 --> 00:05:17.678
And so we call this
interference feature right here,

00:05:17.678 --> 00:05:21.381
we often call it the zero-order
interference feature.

00:05:21.381 --> 00:05:24.088
We call this one,
when N is equal to 1,

00:05:24.088 --> 00:05:26.652
the first-order.
We call this one the

00:05:26.652 --> 00:05:30.000
second-order interference
feature.

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:35.032
And in between the very bright
spots on that screen,

00:05:35.032 --> 00:05:39.671
what we have are dark spots
here, here and here.

00:05:39.671 --> 00:05:45.394
And what I am going to ask you
to do in recitation section,

00:05:45.394 --> 00:05:50.328
actually next Tuesday,
is to look at what condition

00:05:50.328 --> 00:05:56.052
has to apply in order to have
these dark spots which result

00:05:56.052 --> 00:06:01.025
from destructive interference.
And, of course,

00:06:01.025 --> 00:06:03.826
when you analyze that you're
going to see,

00:06:03.826 --> 00:06:06.833
say right here,
the crest, the maximum of one

00:06:06.833 --> 00:06:10.797
wave at the same point in space
as the minimum of the other

00:06:10.797 --> 00:06:13.257
wave.
And you get maximum destructive

00:06:13.257 --> 00:06:15.922
interference everywhere along
that line.

00:06:15.922 --> 00:06:19.681
And what you will do in
recitation next week is actually

00:06:19.681 --> 00:06:24.054
to figure out what the condition
is for destructive interference.

00:06:24.054 --> 00:06:28.223
And that is going to be N plus
one half times lambda.

00:06:28.223 --> 00:06:33.297
So, it is this observation of

00:06:33.297 --> 00:06:40.005
these interference phenomena
that are characteristics of the

00:06:40.005 --> 00:06:44.781
wave-like nature of anything.
In this case,

00:06:44.781 --> 00:06:49.670
the wave-like nature of light,
of radiation.

00:06:49.670 --> 00:06:56.492
On Friday, what we are going to
do is we're going to see this

00:06:56.492 --> 00:07:02.860
same sort of interference
phenomena, a property of waves,

00:07:02.860 --> 00:07:09.000
be observed from particles,
from electrons.

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:13.536
This diagram,
you are going to see once again

00:07:13.536 --> 00:07:16.938
on Friday.
And we will use that to

00:07:16.938 --> 00:07:21.577
demonstrate the wave-like nature
of particles,

00:07:21.577 --> 00:07:25.494
electrons.
That is our evidence for the

00:07:25.494 --> 00:07:32.393
wave-like nature of light.
Now, what we are going to do is

00:07:32.393 --> 00:07:38.195
we're going to talk about the
other behavior of light,

00:07:38.195 --> 00:07:43.887
and that is the particle light
behavior of radiation.

00:07:43.887 --> 00:07:47.390
And I forgot to get out my
notes.

00:07:47.390 --> 00:07:52.754
What is that evidence?
Well, soon after Thompson's

00:07:52.754 --> 00:07:58.665
discovery of the electron,
there were some observations

00:07:58.665 --> 00:08:06.000
being made of something called
the photoelectric effect.

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:11.915
And this was very curious.
The photoelectric effect is

00:08:11.915 --> 00:08:18.946
simply that you have some metal
here and you shine some light on

00:08:18.946 --> 00:08:23.187
that metal.
And what happens is that an

00:08:23.187 --> 00:08:26.089
electron is ejected.
Metal.

00:08:26.089 --> 00:08:31.000
Light coming in.
Electron comes out.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:35.501
But the frequency of this light
that is coming in,

00:08:35.501 --> 00:08:39.818
this frequency nu,
we talked about frequency the

00:08:39.818 --> 00:08:45.238
other day, has to be greater
than or equal to some threshold

00:08:45.238 --> 00:08:50.107
frequency, some threshold
frequency that I am going to

00:08:50.107 --> 00:08:52.863
call nu nought.
In other words,

00:08:52.863 --> 00:08:58.007
if I come in with radiation
here that has got a frequency

00:08:58.007 --> 00:09:03.152
that is less than nu nought,
well, then no electrons come

00:09:03.152 --> 00:09:10.179
off of the metal.
Maybe we could raise the screen

00:09:10.179 --> 00:09:16.651
here for the moment.
Well, another way to kind of

00:09:16.651 --> 00:09:25.146
plot that observation is to just
plot number of electrons versus

00:09:25.146 --> 00:09:31.846
the frequency of the radiation.
And so if you're at low

00:09:31.846 --> 00:09:36.583
frequency, there are going to be
no electrons that come off,

00:09:36.583 --> 00:09:40.518
but then when you get to some
frequency nu nought,

00:09:40.518 --> 00:09:44.291
all of a sudden electrons are
going to come off.

00:09:44.291 --> 00:09:49.029
And the number of electrons
that come off is going to remain

00:09:49.029 --> 00:09:53.124
constant as you increase the
frequency of the light.

00:09:53.124 --> 00:09:57.781
And typically this frequency of
the light that causes these

00:09:57.781 --> 00:10:03.000
electrons to be emitted is in
the ultraviolet range.

00:10:03.000 --> 00:10:07.633
Well, this was a curious
observation in the late 1800s,

00:10:07.633 --> 00:10:11.666
very early 1900s.
And scientists just started to

00:10:11.666 --> 00:10:16.729
measure everything about these
electrons they possibly could

00:10:16.729 --> 00:10:21.448
measure, because they just
didn't understand the effect.

00:10:21.448 --> 00:10:26.683
And one of the things that they
measured is the kinetic energy

00:10:26.683 --> 00:10:31.414
of the electrons.
Here I am going to plot kinetic

00:10:31.414 --> 00:10:34.452
energy, KE.
And they measure the kinetic

00:10:34.452 --> 00:10:39.281
energy of the electrons as the
function of the frequency of the

00:10:39.281 --> 00:10:42.163
light.
Again, at low frequencies there

00:10:42.163 --> 00:10:46.213
is no kinetic energy,
because there are no electrons.

00:10:46.213 --> 00:10:49.484
But then here,
at some frequency nu nought,

00:10:49.484 --> 00:10:54.002
all of a sudden electrons come
out, and lo and behold-- And

00:10:54.002 --> 00:10:57.741
these are points just
representing the individual

00:10:57.741 --> 00:11:01.159
measurements--
Lo and behold,

00:11:01.159 --> 00:11:04.887
as you increase the frequency
above nu nought,

00:11:04.887 --> 00:11:09.195
the kinetic energy increased.
It increased and looked

00:11:09.195 --> 00:11:13.088
directly proportional.
The kinetic energy looked

00:11:13.088 --> 00:11:17.313
directly proportional to the
frequency of the light.

00:11:17.313 --> 00:11:21.538
Well, let me tell you,
that was a big mystery as far

00:11:21.538 --> 00:11:25.017
as classical physical ideas were
concerned.

00:11:25.017 --> 00:11:30.006
That was a big mystery.
Because, in the classical

00:11:30.006 --> 00:11:34.982
physics that was understood at
that time, the kinetic energy of

00:11:34.982 --> 00:11:37.952
the electrons,
KE as a function of the

00:11:37.952 --> 00:11:41.724
frequency of light,
well, that classical physics

00:11:41.724 --> 00:11:46.620
would predict that that kinetic
energy were independent of the

00:11:46.620 --> 00:11:50.874
frequency of the light.
There was nothing in the known

00:11:50.874 --> 00:11:54.806
classical physics,
classical electromagnetism that

00:11:54.806 --> 00:11:59.783
would allow the frequency of the
light to be related in any way

00:11:59.783 --> 00:12:05.000
to the kinetic energy of the
electrons kicked off.

00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:09.991
There was no reason for why
bluer light, which has a higher

00:12:09.991 --> 00:12:14.207
frequency, would eject electrons
and redder light,

00:12:14.207 --> 00:12:19.026
which has a lower frequency
would not eject the electron.

00:12:19.026 --> 00:12:23.501
And classical physics also
predicted that the kinetic

00:12:23.501 --> 00:12:28.664
energy of the electrons should
be dependent on the intensity,

00:12:28.664 --> 00:12:34.000
I am going to call it I,
the intensity of the light.

00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:37.868
In kind of general this sort of
dependence.

00:12:37.868 --> 00:12:42.934
That is, the brighter the
light, the more kinetic energy

00:12:42.934 --> 00:12:46.894
these electrons ought to be
kicked out with.

00:12:46.894 --> 00:12:50.394
In other words,
the brighter the light,

00:12:50.394 --> 00:12:54.815
the more energy you were
putting into that metal.

00:12:54.815 --> 00:12:58.960
And, therefore,
the electrons should be kicked

00:12:58.960 --> 00:13:04.673
out with more energy.
That's what classical physics

00:13:04.673 --> 00:13:07.992
was predicting.
But the measurements,

00:13:07.992 --> 00:13:13.248
go in the lab and you do the
measurement, the measurements

00:13:13.248 --> 00:13:18.226
showed that the kinetic energy
was independent of these

00:13:18.226 --> 00:13:22.283
intensities of light.
This is the experiment.

00:13:22.283 --> 00:13:28.000
It had nothing to do with the
intensity of the light.

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:33.443
The kinetic energy remained the
same no matter how bright that

00:13:33.443 --> 00:13:38.709
light was, not matter how much
energy you were sticking into

00:13:38.709 --> 00:13:41.208
the system.
Now what changed,

00:13:41.208 --> 00:13:46.473
here, as you put more and more
energy or as you put more and

00:13:46.473 --> 00:13:50.489
more intensity,
what changed was the number of

00:13:50.489 --> 00:13:55.219
electrons that came off,
but not their kinetic energy.

00:13:55.219 --> 00:14:00.663
So, this was another conundrum
here, in terms of being able to

00:14:00.663 --> 00:14:07.000
explain it with the known
classical physics at that time.

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:13.944
These data were around for a
few years before Einstein took a

00:14:13.944 --> 00:14:18.805
look at it.
And he looked at these plots of

00:14:18.805 --> 00:14:24.824
the kinetic energy versus the
frequency of the light.

00:14:24.824 --> 00:14:30.148
He looked at it,
for, say, this is the data for

00:14:30.148 --> 00:14:34.936
metal B.
Here is the data for metal A.

00:14:34.936 --> 00:14:39.189
In all cases,
it kind of looked like it was

00:14:39.189 --> 00:14:44.455
linearly dependent on it.
And the only thing that was

00:14:44.455 --> 00:14:49.012
seemingly different,
for the different metals,

00:14:49.012 --> 00:14:52.253
was the threshold frequency
here.

00:14:52.253 --> 00:14:57.113
What Einstein did,
a real leap here of intuition,

00:14:57.113 --> 00:15:04.000
was that he went and he fit a
straight line to this data.

00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:09.541
Well, he did a better job
fitting a straight line than I

00:15:09.541 --> 00:15:12.764
did.
He fit a straight line here.

00:15:12.764 --> 00:15:17.298
Y equals mx plus b,
no problem,

00:15:17.298 --> 00:15:21.731
where kinetic energy is y and x
is nu, right?

00:15:21.731 --> 00:15:25.962
He looked at that and
calculated the slope.

00:15:25.962 --> 00:15:31.000
And he looked at it and he
looked at it.

00:15:31.000 --> 00:15:36.677
And he goes finally,
very interesting,

00:15:36.677 --> 00:15:46.343
because what was so interesting
here was the value of the slope,

00:15:46.343 --> 00:15:52.941
the value of m.
The value of this slope here

00:15:52.941 --> 00:16:00.000
was equal to 6.626x10^-34 joule
seconds.

00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:06.844
No matter what metal he looked
at, the value of the slope was

00:16:06.844 --> 00:16:11.863
6.626x10^-34 joule seconds.
So what, you say?

00:16:11.863 --> 00:16:18.707
Well, it was very interesting
to Einstein, because just a few

00:16:18.707 --> 00:16:24.524
years before there was a
gentleman who was analyzing

00:16:24.524 --> 00:16:30.000
what's called black-body
radiation data.

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:33.440
Let me just explain this a
little bit to you,

00:16:33.440 --> 00:16:36.021
but you're not responsible for
it.

00:16:36.021 --> 00:16:38.992
What is a black-body?
Well, let's just,

00:16:38.992 --> 00:16:42.981
for a simple example,
think about the burner on your

00:16:42.981 --> 00:16:46.421
electric stove.
We will consider that to be a

00:16:46.421 --> 00:16:49.627
black-body.
What you know is that when you

00:16:49.627 --> 00:16:53.303
turn up the voltage,
that the temperature starts

00:16:53.303 --> 00:16:57.917
going up, and at some point the
temperature gets high enough

00:16:57.917 --> 00:17:03.000
such that the burner glows a
little bit dull red.

00:17:03.000 --> 00:17:06.640
And then if you turn it up some
more, it gets hotter,

00:17:06.640 --> 00:17:09.160
the burner glows a little bit
redder.

00:17:09.160 --> 00:17:11.329
That's the black-body
radiation.

00:17:11.329 --> 00:17:14.970
If you turn it up some more,
the burner glows orange.

00:17:14.970 --> 00:17:18.259
Frequency going up.
If you turn it up some more,

00:17:18.259 --> 00:17:21.900
and you better not do this,
the burner starts glowing

00:17:21.900 --> 00:17:24.000
yellow.
And then, if you could,

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:27.079
and you probably cannot turn it
up some more,

00:17:27.079 --> 00:17:31.000
it ultimately is white.
All frequencies.

00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:36.828
Now what scientists had been
doing, is that they had been

00:17:36.828 --> 00:17:43.386
analyzing the intensity of that
radiation from a black-body as a

00:17:43.386 --> 00:17:48.903
function of the frequency.
And they did it for lots of

00:17:48.903 --> 00:17:53.587
different temperatures.
This is our black-body

00:17:53.587 --> 00:17:57.438
radiation.
I am plotting the intensity

00:17:57.438 --> 00:18:00.781
here.
And so they dispersed the

00:18:00.781 --> 00:18:04.631
radiation, they analyzed it as a
function of frequency,

00:18:04.631 --> 00:18:08.836
and what they saw was a curve
that looked kind of like this.

00:18:08.836 --> 00:18:12.044
And this temperature here,
we will call it T1,

00:18:12.044 --> 00:18:15.679
that was for some temperature
T1, a low temperature.

00:18:15.679 --> 00:18:19.599
This isn't in your notes,
because you're not responsible

00:18:19.599 --> 00:18:22.165
for this.
I'm just trying to make the

00:18:22.165 --> 00:18:25.800
importance here of this slope,
or I'm just trying to

00:18:25.800 --> 00:18:30.006
illustrate the importance of
this value for the slope in the

00:18:30.006 --> 00:18:35.352
photoelectric experiment.
And then at a higher

00:18:35.352 --> 00:18:40.764
temperature here,
T2, the intensity got bigger,

00:18:40.764 --> 00:18:46.411
but also the maximum shifted to
higher frequency.

00:18:46.411 --> 00:18:52.529
And at temperature T3,
here now T3 is greater than T2

00:18:52.529 --> 00:18:57.941
and greater than T1,
frequency shifts even to a

00:18:57.941 --> 00:19:03.384
higher frequency.
That was the observation.

00:19:03.384 --> 00:19:06.151
This is dull red,
red, orange,

00:19:06.151 --> 00:19:09.108
etc.
Well, Planck was trying to,

00:19:09.108 --> 00:19:14.546
along with a lot of other
people, understand those curves.

00:19:14.546 --> 00:19:19.411
And he came up with a model.
And the model said that

00:19:19.411 --> 00:19:24.562
materials, these black-bodies,
had oscillators in them.

00:19:24.562 --> 00:19:30.000
And these oscillators were
emitting radiation.

00:19:30.000 --> 00:19:34.875
These oscillators were
responsible for giving off this

00:19:34.875 --> 00:19:38.646
radiation.
And he also added another twist

00:19:38.646 --> 00:19:43.246
to those oscillators in that
those oscillators were

00:19:43.246 --> 00:19:49.041
quantized, that they could only
emit discrete packets of energy.

00:19:49.041 --> 00:19:54.284
And using that basic idea and
something called statistical

00:19:54.284 --> 00:19:59.252
mechanics, he was able to
calculate the shapes of these

00:19:59.252 --> 00:20:03.233
curves.
A lot of his calculation.

00:20:03.233 --> 00:20:08.594
And so this green here is going
to be a calculated curve here

00:20:08.594 --> 00:20:12.525
for T equals 1,
a calculated curve here for T

00:20:12.525 --> 00:20:16.725
equals 2, a calculated curve
here for T equal 3.

00:20:16.725 --> 00:20:21.549
He got the shape right,
but he didn't get the magnitude

00:20:21.549 --> 00:20:24.587
right.
And he said how do I get the

00:20:24.587 --> 00:20:30.163
magnitude right?
Well, what he realized is that

00:20:30.163 --> 00:20:35.435
in that formulation,
what he had to do was multiply

00:20:35.435 --> 00:20:41.551
the frequency of the oscillators
by this constant m or this

00:20:41.551 --> 00:20:46.190
constant that is called h,
Planck's constant.

00:20:46.190 --> 00:20:50.197
Where does Planck's constant
come from?

00:20:50.197 --> 00:20:52.833
From this.
Hey, that's it.

00:20:52.833 --> 00:20:58.000
It is, in a sense,
a fitting constant.

00:20:58.000 --> 00:21:02.402
There isn't any derivation of
Planck's constant.

00:21:02.402 --> 00:21:06.898
You cannot sit down and derive
Planck's constant.

00:21:06.898 --> 00:21:11.112
It is our observation of the
way nature works.

00:21:11.112 --> 00:21:15.327
So that is where Planck's
constant comes from.

00:21:15.327 --> 00:21:19.917
And so you can imagine
Einstein's surprise when he

00:21:19.917 --> 00:21:23.008
analyzed these photoelectron
data.

00:21:23.008 --> 00:21:27.316
And, lo and behold,
out from the data comes the

00:21:27.316 --> 00:21:32.000
same constant that Planck had
found.

00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:38.616
And Einstein realized that
there must be something really

00:21:38.616 --> 00:21:45.232
very fundamental about this h,
about what is now known as

00:21:45.232 --> 00:21:49.130
Planck's constant.
So, he pursued.

00:21:49.130 --> 00:21:55.746
And what he did then was he
just wrote down the equations

00:21:55.746 --> 00:22:03.103
here for that straight line.
That's kinetic energy is equal

00:22:03.103 --> 00:22:08.068
to nu, that is my x,
the slope is h,

00:22:08.068 --> 00:22:14.586
and he found that the intercept
here was minus h times

00:22:14.586 --> 00:22:18.827
nu nought.
So, this will be then plus the

00:22:18.827 --> 00:22:22.758
intercept, or minus h,
times nu nought.

00:22:22.758 --> 00:22:30.000
That was the equation of the
line he fitted through the data.

00:22:30.000 --> 00:22:35.451
Now, he also realized he had
energy units on this side,

00:22:35.451 --> 00:22:40.195
so he better have had energy
units on this side.

00:22:40.195 --> 00:22:45.545
If this is a frequency,
then h must have the unit such

00:22:45.545 --> 00:22:49.381
that h times nu,
this has to be energy.

00:22:49.381 --> 00:22:54.832
And since this is the frequency
of the light coming in,

00:22:54.832 --> 00:22:59.274
this energy E,
that must be the energy of the

00:22:59.274 --> 00:23:04.793
incident light.
And here is where this equation

00:23:04.793 --> 00:23:09.029
E equals h nu comes from.
This is it.

00:23:09.029 --> 00:23:12.453
This is where this equation
comes from.

00:23:12.453 --> 00:23:17.500
What it is telling you is that
the energy of the light is

00:23:17.500 --> 00:23:22.726
proportional to the frequency.
This was the first time that

00:23:22.726 --> 00:23:27.773
there was any indication that
the energy of the light had

00:23:27.773 --> 00:23:33.000
anything to do with the
frequency of the light.

00:23:33.000 --> 00:23:40.061
The very first time.
And what E equals h nu ended up

00:23:40.061 --> 00:23:46.015
being thought of is as a
particle of energy,

00:23:46.015 --> 00:23:52.246
as a packet of energy,
as a quantum of energy,

00:23:52.246 --> 00:23:57.923
as, eventually,
it is going to be called a

00:23:57.923 --> 00:24:02.874
photon.
The photon, this particle or

00:24:02.874 --> 00:24:07.801
packet of energy,
is given by its frequency times

00:24:07.801 --> 00:24:11.701
this constant,
this natural constant h,

00:24:11.701 --> 00:24:15.910
Planck's constant.
You could have here any

00:24:15.910 --> 00:24:21.864
frequency of light you wanted,
but the energy of that light

00:24:21.864 --> 00:24:27.715
only comes in chunks given by
this quantization constant h

00:24:27.715 --> 00:24:33.837
times that frequency.
I will explain that a little

00:24:33.837 --> 00:24:37.587
more in just a moment.
Well, likewise,

00:24:37.587 --> 00:24:42.959
this h times nu nought here,
that better be an energy,

00:24:42.959 --> 00:24:46.202
also.
And so what that h times nu

00:24:46.202 --> 00:24:50.763
nought is,
is the threshold energy.

00:24:50.763 --> 00:24:56.743
Since nu nought was a threshold
frequency, h times nu nought

00:24:56.743 --> 00:25:03.970
better be the threshold energy.
And let's try to understand

00:25:03.970 --> 00:25:08.369
that in terms of an energy level
diagram.

